  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Preheat the oven to 180°C fan."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Chop your aubergines into 3cm thick chunks and dice your red onion."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a large bowl, toss the aubergine with the vegetable oil, ½ tsp of the ground turmeric and a generous pinch of salt. Spread on a large roasting tray in a single layer and roast for 15 mins, tossing every 5 minutes or so."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, heat 2 tbsp coconut oil in a large frying pan over a medium heat. Add the mustard and fenugreek seeds."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once the mustard seeds stop crackling, add the cinnamon stick, curry leaves, onion, garlic, ginger, lemongrass and dried chillies. Stir well to coat in the oil, add a pinch of salt and continue to cook for 8-10 mins, stirring occasionally until the onions are soft and translucent."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the curry powder and remaining ½ tsp ground turmeric and cook for a further minute, adding a splash of water if they begin to stick to the pan."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the coconut milk, stock and tamarind, reduce the heat to low and cook 3-4 mins until the liquid has reduced to half."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Stir through the roasted aubergine and sugar and continue to simmer for 3 mins, then season to taste with salt."
    },
    {
      "heading": "For the Roti",
      "description": "Finely chop your red onion, green chilli and curry leaves."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your chopped chillies and onion to a large mixing bowl along with your flour, curry leaves, coconut oil, and desiccated coconut. Mix the ingredients together, adding a little warm water at a time, to bring together a cohesive dough that does not stick to the hands. The dough should have the consistency of play-dough."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Knead for about 5 minutes by hand. There’s no need to use a stand mixer for this."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Leave to rest at room temperature, covered with cling film for at least 30 mins, or longer if preparing ahead."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Roll out into 6-inch discs the thickness of two stacked one pound coins. I prefer a slightly rough, natural look rather than perfect circles."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat a dry non-stick pan or well-seasoned cast-iron pan over high heat and then reduce heat to medium and cook the rotis for 4-5 mins flipping halfway through (The key is not to use oil or fat when cooking the rotis and to cook them on a hot dry pan)."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve immediately with your curry or store in a box wrapped in a clean kitchen towel."
    }
  ],
